---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Find Legal Help" description="Free and low-cost immigration legal help resources: national nonprofits, law school clinics, and how to avoid notario fraud.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-8" data-pagefind-body>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Find Legal Help</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
      The resources below are free or low-cost. This list is not an endorsement, and we are not affiliated with any of these organizations. Always verify an attorney's credentials before sharing personal information.
    </p>

    <!-- National nonprofits -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">National nonprofits</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-5">
        <li class="border-l-2 border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 pl-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            <a href="https://immigrationlawhelp.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">
              Immigration Legal Resource Center — immigrationlawhelp.org
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-1">
            A searchable directory of free and low-cost immigration legal service providers across the United States, operated by the Immigration Advocates Network.
          </p>
          <span class="inline-block text-xs bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900/40 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mt-1">Legal directory</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-2 border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 pl-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            <a href="https://www.clinic.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">
              Catholic Legal Immigration Network (CLINIC)
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-1">
            One of the largest networks of nonprofit immigration legal service providers in the country, with more than 400 affiliate programs in 49 states.
          </p>
          <span class="inline-block text-xs bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900/40 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mt-1">National nonprofit network</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-2 border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 pl-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            <a href="https://www.aila.org/practice/pro-bono" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">
              AILA National Pro Bono Program
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-1">
            The American Immigration Lawyers Association coordinates pro bono immigration legal representation. Use their directory to find pro bono clinics and participating attorneys.
          </p>
          <span class="inline-block text-xs bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900/40 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mt-1">Pro bono referrals</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-2 border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 pl-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            <a href="https://www.nilc.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">
              National Immigration Law Center (NILC)
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-1">
            Focuses on advocacy and litigation for low-income immigrants, and provides referrals to legal service organizations.
          </p>
          <span class="inline-block text-xs bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900/40 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mt-1">Advocacy / referrals</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Law school clinics -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">Law school clinics</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-4">Law school immigration clinics provide free representation under the supervision of licensed attorneys. Availability and case types vary by school.</p>
      <ul class="space-y-5">
        <li class="border-l-2 border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 pl-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            <a href="https://law.yale.edu/clinics/immigration-clinic" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">
              Yale Law School — Jerome N. Frank Legal Services Organization
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-1">Provides free legal services in immigration and other matters to low-income clients in Connecticut.</p>
          <span class="inline-block text-xs bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/40 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mt-1">Law school clinic</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-2 border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 pl-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            <a href="https://www.law.harvard.edu/academics/clinical/ij/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">
              Harvard Law School — Immigration and Refugee Clinical Program
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-1">Represents asylum seekers, refugees, and undocumented individuals in removal proceedings and related matters.</p>
          <span class="inline-block text-xs bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/40 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mt-1">Law school clinic</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-2 border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 pl-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            <a href="https://law.georgetown.edu/experiential-learning/clinics/immigration-clinic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">
              Georgetown University Law Center — Immigration Clinic
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-1">Represents low-income immigrants in the DC metropolitan area in removal defense, asylum, and relief from removal.</p>
          <span class="inline-block text-xs bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/40 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mt-1">Law school clinic</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-2 border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 pl-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            <a href="https://www.law.nyu.edu/academics/clinics/immigrantrights" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">
              NYU School of Law — Immigrant Rights Clinic
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-1">Provides direct representation and engages in policy advocacy on behalf of immigrants in New York.</p>
          <span class="inline-block text-xs bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/40 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mt-1">Law school clinic</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-2 border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 pl-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            <a href="https://law.uchicago.edu/clinics/immigration" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">
              University of Chicago Law School — Immigration Clinic
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-1">Provides free legal representation to immigrants in Chicago and surrounding areas.</p>
          <span class="inline-block text-xs bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/40 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mt-1">Law school clinic</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Verify credentials -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">Verify someone's credentials</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Only licensed attorneys and <a href="https://www.justice.gov/eoir/recognition-accreditation-roster-reports" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">DOJ-accredited representatives</a> are authorized to provide immigration legal services for a fee. You can verify whether someone is on the DOJ EOIR accredited representative roster using the link above.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        To verify an attorney's license, look up your state bar association's attorney directory. Most state bars have online lookup tools.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Notario fraud -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">Red flags: notario fraud and immigration scams</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Immigration fraud — including "notario fraud" — is a serious problem. A notario (or "notario público") in many Latin American countries is a licensed legal professional, but in the United States the title has no legal meaning and does not qualify someone to provide immigration legal advice.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-slate-200 mb-2">Warning signs of a scam:</p>
      <ul class="text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300 space-y-1 text-sm pl-5 list-disc mb-4">
        <li>Promises to "fix" your immigration status quickly or guarantees a specific outcome</li>
        <li>Asks you to sign blank forms</li>
        <li>Refuses to give you copies of documents filed on your behalf</li>
        <li>Claims to have special connections at USCIS or an immigration court</li>
        <li>Is not a licensed attorney or DOJ-accredited representative but still charges for immigration help</li>
        <li>Uses titles like "notario," "notario público," "immigration consultant," or "visa consultant" and charges for legal advice</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-sm">
        Resources:
        <a href="https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/topics/immigration-services" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">FTC — Immigration Services Fraud</a>
        &bull;
        <a href="https://www.uscis.gov/avoid-scams" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900 dark:hover:text-blue-300">USCIS — Avoid Scams</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
